    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan:\n\n## Model Rename Feature — Implementation Plan\n\n**4 files to modify, no new files, no test files touched.**\n\n### What gets added\n\n| Layer | Change |\n|---|---|\n| `api/types.go` | `RenameRequest{Source, Destination}` struct — mirrors `CopyRequest` exactly |\n| `api/client.go` | `Rename()` method — calls `POST /api/rename`, identical pattern to `Copy()` |\n| `server/routes.go` | `RenameHandler` + `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", ...)` route registration |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | `RenameHandler` CLI func + `renameCmd` cobra command (`ollama rename SOURCE DEST`) |\n\n### Handler logic (the interesting part)\n\nThe `RenameHandler` in `server/routes.go`:\n1. Parses + validates source and destination names (same as `CopyHandler`)\n2. **404**: `manifest.PathForName(src)` → `os.Stat` → not found → `http.StatusNotFound`\n3. **409**: `manifest.PathForName(dst)` → `os.Stat` → exists → `http.StatusConflict`\n4. Calls existing `CopyModel(src, dst)` (reuses `server/images.go:397`)\n5. Deletes the source via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` (same pattern as `DeleteHandler`)\n\nEverything reuses existing utilities — no new helper functions needed.",
